us on supported classic actor APIs such as ActorSystem, Props, Actor, serialization, ReflectiveDynamicAccess, and DNS settings. If retaining DNS default-name-server fallback coverage, preserve the existing JVM/native-image export setting --add-exports=java.base/sun.net.dns=ALL-UNNAMED.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Adding pekko-actor-typed_2.13 would test a different Pekko module and still would not provide the removed org.apache.pekko.actor.TypedActor API.\",\n    \"Pekko documentation lists pekko-testkit_2.13 as the normal test helper for classic actor tests, but it is not required to reach meaningful reachability-metadata coverage and should only be added if generated tests deliberately use TestKit/TestProbe APIs.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0d5a851e8d045fe4016a40352fb9ec81938674660c5ebaf32b\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1057, "output": 1088, "cacheRead": 37376, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 39521, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782592804560, "responseId": "resp_0d5a851e8d045fe4016a40352500bc8193a3360c0b09590895"}, "toolResults": []}
